Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.72,0:00:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My theme for this month’s broadcast is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.29,0:00:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“Young Ones\N—Build Your Future With Jehovah!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.43,0:00:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do, \N1 Timothy 6:19 assures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.27,0:00:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that you will \N‘safely treasure up for yourself \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.60,0:00:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a fine foundation for the future,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.44,0:00:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will \N“get a firm hold on the real life.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.88,0:00:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, we will be directing \Nmany of our comments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.15,0:00:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,directly to you dear young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.29,0:00:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jehovah’s organization.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.09,0:00:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, if we think about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.26,0:00:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us figuratively \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.43,0:00:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,are very young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.60,0:00:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,compared to eternity\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.33,0:00:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,—how long we hope to live. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.07,0:00:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in a sense, \Nour comments during this broadcast \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.67,0:01:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,have application to all of us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.31,0:01:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally, I am so thankful to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.18,0:01:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that positive peer pressure \Nwas put on me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.95,0:01:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to enter the pioneer ministry \Nright out of high school. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.26,0:01:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What a blessing and a protection \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.69,0:01:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it was to enter \Nthe regular pioneer work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.60,0:01:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,at age 17 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.83,0:01:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be able to go to Bethel at 18. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.27,0:01:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though there was considerable \Nworldly pressure put on me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.07,0:01:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to pursue university education, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.14,0:01:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I am so happy that with Jehovah’s help, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.52,0:01:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to build my future \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.19,0:01:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.19,0:01:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly, I have no regrets. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.32,0:01:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is always true of young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.33,0:01:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,who serve Jehovah from their hearts\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.87,0:01:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,—they have no regrets. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.33,0:02:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you will enjoy \Nthese expressions from young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.07,0:02:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who are building \Ntheir future with Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.53,0:02:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I started pioneering, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.53,0:02:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really nervous that I wouldn’t be able \Nto get my time in every month.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.24,0:02:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a bit hard when I started pioneering \Nbecause I didn’t have a car.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.21,0:02:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My boss, \Nhe didn’t give me part-time work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.61,0:02:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I found it really hard \Nto balance schoolwork \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.91,0:02:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and pioneering \Nat the same time.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.98,0:02:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,My biggest struggle was fear of man, \Nso that really hindered me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.32,0:02:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,because I wasn’t very good \Nat talking to people.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.62,0:02:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a good routine was a struggle.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.52,0:02:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,My brother and I are \Nthe only ones in the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.16,0:02:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My family didn’t understand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.50,0:02:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,why we wanted to go preaching.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.33,0:02:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t think \Nthat I’d make a good pioneer.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.57,0:02:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve had Type 1 diabetes \Nsince I was five. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.47,0:02:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was always worried \Nabout whether or not \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.61,0:02:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I could balance that health condition \Nwith pioneering.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.08,0:03:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The challenges \Ndon’t seem that big now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.55,0:03:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but back at that time \Nthey were a really big deal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.28,0:03:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But the coolest thing \Nwas how Jehovah helped me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.95,0:03:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer to Jehovah \Nhelped me overcome my fears.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.92,0:03:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,My family was \Na massive help from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.03,0:03:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Because my dad was the one \Nwho first encouraged me to pioneer, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.89,0:03:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,when I did start pioneering, \Nhe promised that I would have \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.30,0:03:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the full support of my family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.20,0:03:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When I spoke to brothers and sisters \Nwho spent their youth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.17,0:03:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the full-time service \Nthat really helped me\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.84,0:03:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was really encouraging, \Nand it really motivated me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.11,0:03:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to want to make my own memories \Nand my own experiences \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.71,0:03:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in the full-time service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.61,0:03:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So there were \Npractical things I could do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.85,0:03:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t have a car; \NI just walked or I caught the bus.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.22,0:03:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to work out \Nwhat my priorities were first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.86,0:03:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had to find out how many hours \Nwould I have to go witnessing every week. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.99,0:03:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I just sat down \Nand I looked at every day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.13,0:03:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and planned out which days \NI could go witnessing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.13,0:03:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which days I had to go to school, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.13,0:03:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and also allocated time \Nso that I could do my homework and study.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.24,0:03:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a schedule \Nwas really good \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.00,0:04:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because I could see it \Nall out in front of me,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.01,0:04:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and I could see \Nthat the hour requirement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.01,0:04:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,was actually attainable, \Nso that made it a lot less daunting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.88,0:04:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I first set short-term goals of pioneering \Nin the special months of activity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.08,0:04:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I was able \Nto begin continuous auxiliary, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.69,0:04:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and then eventually \NI started regular pioneering.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.46,0:04:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the best things I did \Nto prepare myself for pioneering \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.69,0:04:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,was to auxiliary pioneer beforehand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.79,0:04:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It really set me up \Nto be able to overcome \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.43,0:04:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,any challenges \Nthat I faced while I was pioneering.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.47,0:04:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought about Malachi 3:10. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.10,0:04:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I trusted in Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.10,0:04:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but this was my chance \Nto test him out.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.64,0:04:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed, \Nput my trust in Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.28,0:04:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and put my application in.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.31,0:04:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,After my form \Nwas in for pioneering, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.88,0:04:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a brother, with time, \Na brother called me and offered me work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.15,0:04:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I had unemployment \Nfor three months, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.32,0:04:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,which wasn’t a good time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.59,0:04:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But during that time, \NI had Jehovah as my main focus. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.89,0:04:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he supported me, \Nand he didn’t let me down.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.23,0:04:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Asking brothers and sisters to come \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.23,0:05:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and work with me, \Nmaybe on days that I knew \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.30,0:05:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that I wouldn’t get as much support, \Nreally helped. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.57,0:05:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That helped me to organize \Nmy hours a little bit more, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.61,0:05:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and also I’d get to know \Nmy brothers and sisters more as well.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.88,0:05:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the greatest joys of pioneering \Nhas been to pioneer with Mum. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.68,0:05:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And we had the privilege of going \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.25,0:05:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to the pioneer school together, \Nwhich was really special.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.95,0:05:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 16:8 reminds me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.99,0:05:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah is right beside me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.06,0:05:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When I’m preaching, \Nit’s like Jehovah is holding my hand.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.26,0:05:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So with full-time service, \NI love making Jehovah happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.37,0:05:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,With everything that he has given me, \NI’m finally able to give something back.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.10,0:05:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking back\N—pioneering—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.97,0:05:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the best decision \NI’ve ever made. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.81,0:05:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s opened up \Nso many different avenues \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.84,0:05:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of service to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.68,0:05:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and it helped me also \Nto have that real desire \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.68,0:05:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to want to stay \Nin full-time service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.18,0:05:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Helping someone \Non the road to everlasting life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.75,0:05:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s the best feeling ever; \Nand it’s really irreplaceable.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.76,0:06:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing I can say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.16,0:06:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“As a young person, start pioneering!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.68,0:06:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What a fine attitude \Nthose young ones have! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.36,0:06:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They are clearly following \Nin Jesus’ footsteps. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus was the wisest man \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.33,0:06:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,who ever walked the earth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.33,0:06:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He could’ve pursued any career \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.37,0:06:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and truly excelled at it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.37,0:06:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He could’ve been \Nthe greatest carpenter who ever lived. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.01,0:06:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.01,0:06:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,he helped his Father \Nbuild the physical universe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.92,0:06:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine \Nwhat kind of houses he could’ve built? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.19,0:06:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Or what if he had pursued \Nbeing an inventor? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.83,0:06:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,With his perfect brain, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.29,0:06:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,he probably could’ve invented \Nthe telephone, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.23,0:06:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,automobile, or computer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.60,0:06:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in the first century. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.70,0:07:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Or what about becoming \Na businessman? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.84,0:07:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,With perfect intelligence, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.74,0:07:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,he likely could’ve come out on top \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.68,0:07:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of every business transaction \Nthat he entered, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.18,0:07:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming the richest businessman \Nwho ever lived. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.02,0:07:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Or have you ever thought about \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.82,0:07:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,if he had pursued becoming \Nan athlete? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.36,0:07:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And excelling in athletic contests \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.43,0:07:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,was a huge endeavor in Jesus’ day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.10,0:07:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,With a little training, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.07,0:07:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it is likely that his perfect body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.04,0:07:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,would have outperformed all people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.71,0:07:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with imperfect bodies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.98,0:07:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,enabling him to become \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.45,0:07:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the most famous athlete who ever lived. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.25,0:07:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Or one more example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.52,0:07:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what if he had decided to become a doctor? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.76,0:07:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He could cure sick people\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.73,0:08:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—even raise the dead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.03,0:08:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine how much \Nhe could’ve charged rich people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.03,0:08:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to raise their dead loved ones? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.67,0:08:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jesus pursued none of these careers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.11,0:08:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.11,0:08:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he knew \Nthat any of such endeavors \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.48,0:08:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,would have only very limited \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.35,0:08:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and temporary benefits. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.25,0:08:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, he pursued something \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.49,0:08:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,he knew would bring far-reaching \Nand everlasting benefits: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.46,0:08:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the full-time ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.33,0:08:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is how the wisest man \Nwho ever walked the earth—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.44,0:08:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is how he reasoned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.70,0:08:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we are wise if we strive to think \Nthe same way.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.64,0:08:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes me think of the comments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.45,0:08:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of a well-adjusted teenage brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.55,0:08:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,whom we served \Nwhile in the circuit work many years ago. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.49,0:09:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This young brother went straight into \Nthe regular pioneer work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.16,0:09:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,out of high school, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.16,0:09:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and I asked him why he did so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.83,0:09:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He explained that he knew \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.50,0:09:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,he could’ve gotten a full-time secular job \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.94,0:09:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and bought a new car for himself, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.67,0:09:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but he reasoned that in a few years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.54,0:09:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that car would rust out and break down, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.08,0:09:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and he would have nothing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.32,0:09:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But he knew that he could go \Ninto the pioneer work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.39,0:09:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and build a close relationship with Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.73,0:09:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and perhaps even find \Nan honest-hearted person\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.33,0:09:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,, and be able to teach that one the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.30,0:09:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And he knew that would last forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.57,0:09:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that is some wise thinking \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.81,0:09:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,on the part of that young brother. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.58,0:09:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And today, that brother \Nhas a beautiful Christian wife \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.05,0:09:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and several spiritual children, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.52,0:10:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and he is serving as a fine elder.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.45,0:10:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you young ones \Nare going to think this way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.06,0:10:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and continue to pursue spiritual goals, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.49,0:10:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it is vital that you wisely choose \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.10,0:10:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,your associates. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.40,0:10:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In a sense, our associates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.97,0:10:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,can be likened to an elevator. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.44,0:10:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we mean? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.41,0:10:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they can take you up \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.11,0:10:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,or they can take you down. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.85,0:10:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If you choose wisely, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.12,0:10:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,they will take you up\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.42,0:10:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—elevate your good qualities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.12,0:10:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and make you a better person. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.29,0:10:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you choose poorly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.63,0:10:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they will take you down. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.40,0:10:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Depending on how badly you choose, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.87,0:10:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they can take you way down\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.17,0:10:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,—to the basement, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.34,0:10:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,even the subbasement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.64,0:11:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,At Proverbs 13:20, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.18,0:11:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,our loving heavenly Father, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,who made us, \Nexplains how it works. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.58,0:11:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah tells us there: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“The one walking with the wise \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.79,0:11:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“will become wise, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.56,0:11:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“but the one \Nwho has dealings with the stupid \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.80,0:11:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,will fare badly.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.10,0:11:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“Walking with” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.10,0:11:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and “having dealings with” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.47,0:11:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,mean “associating with.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.91,0:11:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And who are the “stupid” ones? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.11,0:11:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this scripture contrasts \Nsuch a person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.75,0:11:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with those who are wise. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.98,0:11:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not talking about someone \Nwho lacks mental intellect. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.92,0:11:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It is talking about someone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.36,0:11:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,who does not make \Nwise decisions spiritually \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.23,0:11:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,from Jehovah’s standpoint. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.80,0:11:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we think about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.83,0:11:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone who is not really serving Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.80,0:12:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—at least right now—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.80,0:12:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that one is unwise indeed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.71,0:12:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we associate closely with such ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.75,0:12:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah says that we “will fare badly.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.95,0:12:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We could use another illustration. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.29,0:12:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about someone who is physically sick \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.76,0:12:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and is running a high fever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.56,0:12:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If we spend a lot of time with that person, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.23,0:12:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we will probably catch the same sickness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.13,0:12:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Or worse, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.17,0:12:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,if we spend a lot of time \Nnear a dead body—a corpse—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.61,0:12:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,we will probably pick up a disease. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.45,0:12:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it is similar \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.91,0:12:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,with spending time with a person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.42,0:12:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who is spiritually sick, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.55,0:12:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,or worse, spiritually dead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.99,0:12:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.19,0:12:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,if we choose as our associates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.66,0:13:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,those who love Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.90,0:13:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and who are building \Ntheir everlasting future with Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.97,0:13:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we will benefit greatly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.97,0:13:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Please observe carefully \Nthis variety of young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.95,0:13:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,who are busy storing up \Ntreasures in heaven \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.28,0:13:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.77,0:15:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How heartwarming it is to us\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.37,0:15:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,—and we know it is to Jehovah—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.07,0:15:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to see these beautiful young people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.34,0:15:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,doing what Jesus encourages  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.71,0:15:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,at Matthew 6:20, 21. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.42,0:15:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There, Jesus encourages: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.35,0:15:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“Store up for yourselves \Ntreasures in heaven,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.59,0:15:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“where neither moth nor rust consumes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.66,0:15:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“and where thieves do not break in and steal.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.00,0:15:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“For where your treasure is, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.77,0:15:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there your heart will be also.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.11,0:16:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we think about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.28,0:16:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in the final analysis, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.05,0:16:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,after all is said and done, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.35,0:16:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,whether we are younger or older,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.95,0:16:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,, our net worth will be \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.19,0:16:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,what we have stored up \Nin heaven with Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.89,0:16:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We will not be able to take \Nmaterial treasures with us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.93,0:16:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,through the great tribulation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.16,0:16:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we die, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.23,0:16:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we certainly will not be able to take \Nmaterial treasures with us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.47,0:16:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but we can take spiritual treasures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.61,0:16:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with us through the great tribulation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.78,0:16:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and even through death and resurrection. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.71,0:16:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It is true with all of Jehovah’s people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.12,0:16:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is with the anointed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.49,0:16:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what is stated at Revelation 14:13. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.72,0:16:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It says there: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.76,0:16:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“The things they did go right with them.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.56,0:16:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And how encouraging it is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.03,0:17:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to see young ones getting baptized\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.34,0:17:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,—publicly demonstrating \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.01,0:17:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are giving their lives to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.34,0:17:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And we sincerely hope \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.55,0:17:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that you young ones \Nwho are not yet baptized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.82,0:17:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,will not hold back from getting baptized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.12,0:17:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,as soon as you qualify. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.16,0:17:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The sooner you can get baptized, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.73,0:17:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the sooner you will receive \Ngreater protection \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.40,0:17:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and blessings from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.50,0:17:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Not long ago, \Nit made me very happy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.54,0:17:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to observe a little ten-year-old brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.44,0:17:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,get baptized!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.44,0:17:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And young ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.48,0:17:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,never be afraid to identify yourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.32,0:17:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,as one of Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.49,0:17:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Never allow the fear \Nof what others may think \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.96,0:17:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to cause you to hesitate to do so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.03,0:18:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah tells us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.03,0:18:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,at Proverbs 29:25: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.83,0:18:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Trembling at men is a snare, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.37,0:18:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“but the one trusting in Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.14,0:18:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,will be protected.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.98,0:18:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Many years ago when I was in school, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.08,0:18:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember being \Nat times somewhat worried \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.99,0:18:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,about how my fellow classmates \Nwould view me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.66,0:18:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But then a little while later, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.43,0:18:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I got out of school \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.46,0:18:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and never ever again even saw \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.63,0:18:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,most of those former classmates. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.57,0:18:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it dawned on me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.47,0:18:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that it doesn’t really matter \Nwhat people think about us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.98,0:18:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It is Jehovah’s rating of us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.81,0:18:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that truly counts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.21,0:18:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans cannot add \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.32,0:18:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,even five seconds to our lifespan, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.65,0:19:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah can add \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.82,0:19:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,or subtract eternity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.46,0:19:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And he alone \Ncan also give us true happiness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.00,0:19:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And as Proverbs 29:25 indicates, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.20,0:19:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,what a protection \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.34,0:19:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it is to courageously identify ourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.18,0:19:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,as one of Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.98,0:19:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,fully trusting Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.48,0:19:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and taking our stand solidly with him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.72,0:19:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Never be ashamed of who you are. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.56,0:19:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You are one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.13,0:19:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And please, dear young ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.67,0:19:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we warmly encourage you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.40,0:19:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to listen to those who love you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.17,0:19:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah loves you very much; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.91,0:19:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the Governing Body loves you very much; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.11,0:20:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the elders love you very much; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.25,0:20:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,your Christian parents love you very much. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.89,0:20:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And these ones will tell you the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.42,0:20:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,even though at times \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.43,0:20:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it may not be what you want to hear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.10,0:20:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They will not ‘tickle your ears,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.43,0:20:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps like ones at school \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.23,0:20:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,or in the neighborhood \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.27,0:20:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,who don’t really love you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.67,0:20:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or have your best interests at heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.01,0:20:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But please believe those \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.98,0:20:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,who will tell you the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.51,0:20:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because they love you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.88,0:20:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And never view \NJehovah’s laws and principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.59,0:20:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as depriving you of something good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.86,0:20:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,View them as protecting you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.43,0:20:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,from what will hurt you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.90,0:20:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you recall, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.00,0:20:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan convinced Eve \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.57,0:20:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that she was being deprived by Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.87,0:21:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and was missing out on something good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.58,0:21:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it is true that Eve \Nwas missing out on something. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.45,0:21:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But what was she really missing out on? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.58,0:21:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A tormented conscience, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.55,0:21:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,her beautiful hair turning gray, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.39,0:21:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,her teeth falling out, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.89,0:21:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,her perfect skin wrinkling up like a prune, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.70,0:21:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,being bent over from old age, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.60,0:21:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,hobbling around on a cane, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.60,0:21:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally dying! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.64,0:21:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But Satan convinced her \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.48,0:21:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah was depriving her, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.85,0:21:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so foolishly she reached out to get \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.72,0:21:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what she thought she was missing out on. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.26,0:21:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Satan will try to use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.19,0:21:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the same kind of strategy on you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.30,0:21:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but please don’t let him do it!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.74,0:22:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This also makes me think \Nof an experience a brother once related. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.27,0:22:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that he was visiting \Nan animal observatory, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.41,0:22:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and a large lion lunged toward him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.35,0:22:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but was prevented from reaching him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.05,0:22:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,by a thick glass pane \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.79,0:22:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,separating the animals from the observers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.56,0:22:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,As the lion stood on his hind legs, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.70,0:22:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,clawing the glass \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.23,0:22:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and baring his massive teeth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.37,0:22:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the brother came to realize in a special way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.97,0:22:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the protective value of that barrier. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.21,0:22:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Previously, he said \Nthat he somewhat viewed the glass pane \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.62,0:22:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,as a restriction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.85,0:22:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because the smudges on it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.59,0:22:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,partially blurred his view, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.69,0:22:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but now he viewed it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.69,0:23:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,as a real protection. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.90,0:23:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in a similar way, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.90,0:23:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah doesn’t want Satan, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.40,0:23:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,who is described \Nas ‘a roaring, devouring lion’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.17,0:23:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Peter 5:8— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.18,0:23:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t want him \Nto gobble down you young ones. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.82,0:23:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And His laws and principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.52,0:23:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are designed to keep that \Nfrom happening to you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.42,0:23:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So please listen to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.33,0:23:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He loves you!\N
